A K-Thriller Drama for BLACKSWAN   Title: â€œThe Rise of BLACKSWANâ€  In the bustling city of Seoul, four young women from different backgrounds come together to form the K-pop girl group BLACKSWAN. Fatou, Sriya, Nvee, and Gabi all have one thing in common: their passion for music and their dream of becoming stars.  The pilot episode follows the girls as they navigate the cut-throat world of the Korean music industry. From gruelling practice sessions to dealing with the pressure of being in the public eye, the girls must learn to work together and support each other if they want to make it to the top.  As they prepare for their debut performance, tensions rise and conflicts emerge. Fatou clashes with their manager over creative differences. Sriya struggles with homesickness and misses her family back in India. Nvee must confront her insecurities about her singing abilities. And Gabi finds herself dealing with a dangerous situation when she discovers she is being stalked by an obsessive K-pop stan. The Fans suspect an EX Member of the Group. But is it?  But despite the challenges they face, the girls remain determined to succeed. With their debut performance approaching, they must come together and give it their all if they want to prove to the world that they have what it takes to be the next big thing in K-pop.  Will BLACKSWAN rise to the top or will they crumble under the Pressure?   BLACKSWAN FIGHTING! I'm Indian and i have studied this field for a while now and have few suggestions for u!  1) the outfits were amazing but i felt the vibe of the song is more bold and the indian fits are more relaxed and cultural ,so u should have gone with some dark coloured clothings instead of pastels. 2) the indian dance and everything was worderful but as the song represents karma, i felt u should have shown the indian dance with more expression typa performance on the calm note. 3) the colours added a good touch ,i liked that part.  4) the choreography was shown less and alot of spot light was given individually, which is good but it felt very soft when the music beats are kinda high , a amazing choreography with different angle shots would have done better than spotlights. 5) at last , i would suggest u don't stick to one place like i could see u guys were trying to show beauty of India but instead of like the roads and auto if u would have chosen like wide alley or jungle type of area if would fit the representation better.

The monument that the music video was shot in is known as Dhauli Shanti Stupa which lies to the south of Bhubaneswar, capital city of Odisha. Now some interesting facts about it...  In the year 272 B.C. the great Maurya dynasty's legendary king "Ashoka the Great" looked down from over the vast expanse of the battle field of Kalinga (now the area around Dhauli) littered with bodies after a fierce battle. Even after a well-fought victory, the sight of the aftermath of the war, death and destruction horrified him and resulted in Ashoka's transformation. He became a Buddhist and started following Buddhaâ€™s teachings and austere ways of leading life.

Love from Odisha ğŸ‰â¤
Odisha is the land of Buddha where Buddhism flourished for centuries. Odisha was the sacred land to host Buddha holy hair relic until the land was gone to nonBuddhist rulers and that beautiful ancient history buried under the ground. Even today, the famous Buddhist universities like Lalitagiri, Ratnagiri and Udaygiri still witness the great influence of Buddhism. Buddhist monks from China and other kingdoms visited Odisha and studied in Buddhist universities. Thank you  Blackswan and Sriya Lenka for showing that lost history of Buddhism through the Shanti stupa and also showing the vivid culture of India.

The majestic white building at 00:00:25 is Dhauligiri (Peace pagoda).  It commemorates the place where the great Kalinga war was fought in approx. 200 B.C between the Kalinga kingdom and the Mauryan emperor Ashoka the great.    Although, Asoka won the war, he was so filled with regret with the bloodshed of this war that he converted to Buddhism and this was one of the most consequential events in Indian history and perhaps World history.  Asoka had a long fruitful career ruling over the Mauryan kingdom (which covered almost the whole of present-day India, Pakistan, Bangladesh etc) for the next 40 years.  He sent Buddhist missionaries to almost every big kingdom and he is perhaps, the principal reason Buddhism spread out from India into China, Sri Lanka, Thailand and Tibet and other places in East Asia.

Yes!   Edit : there's a reply to my comment that said they should go international at this point. I kind of agree, it can be a brilliant idea if done right. The girls can still make kpop music from time to time, while reaching wider audience.    I said from time to time since their strength in the first place WAS being a "unique" kpop group. Going off the kpop platform and more towards international truly has the potential advantage of gaining more fans worldwide, but it also has the risk of the group being too generalized by singing english ( most songs in the music industry uses english, and it can get pretty boring )  Maybe they can be an international group and make songs with mixed languages ?
